description.value: Ostracon with the 'Instruction of Amennakht': limestone ostracon painted with twelve lines of hieratic. This copy is well written on a carefully chosen ostracon and the scribe's handwriting seems modelled on Amennakht's own. It was certainly an exercise, since the date is written in red under the final line, as was a common practice of apprentices. The red points mark the ends of lines of verse; in 11. 9-10 a mistake has been made, and there is one point too many (similar mistakes occurs in 11.5 and 6).
